$ Oracle Optimizer: System statistics
@ system statistics

System statistics describe I/O and CPU characteristics and provides a basis for estimating related performance (storage subsystems such as NAS, SAN, JOBD or flash, and CPU).

System statistics are stored in `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/base-tables/aux_stats`.

Oracle → https://docs.oracle.com/en/database/oracle/oracle-database/23/tgsql/gathering-optimizer-statistics.html#GUID-BABC67C0-F851-4849-906E-E2588CFD7F2B[recommends using defaults] for system statistics,
unless there is a good reason to gather them manually.

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/optimizer/statistics

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/stats/api/nouns/stats/system/gather`

  The parameter `→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/optimizer/cost/model` specifies how system statistics are used.

links:
  Nigel Bayliss: → https://blogs.oracle.com/optimizer/post/should-you-gather-system-statistics[Should You Gather System Statistics?]
